"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130879","Women and Equalities","false","2019-06-19","<p>The Equality Act 2010 contains clear, enforceable protections to prevent people from being discriminated against or harassed because of a disability in the provision of services. A person with HIV is automatically protected under the Act because this condition is specified as a disability in the Act.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130879/answer",,,,,,"2019-06-19T14:37:36.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130879/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130879/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2019-06-10","HIV Infection: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps she is taking to ensure that people with HIV are not discriminated against when seeking tattoo, piercings and other similar services.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","262416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130880","Treasury","false","2019-06-13","<p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) introduced rules in 2015 to require contract-based pension providers to set up independent governance committees (IGCs) to address poor consumer outcomes.</p><p>IGCs have a duty to scrutinise the value for money of the provider’s workplace personal pension schemes, taking into account transaction costs, raising concerns and making recommendations to the provider’s board as appropriate. IGCs have a duty to assess whether all the investment choices available, including default options, are suitable for the interests of consumers.</p><p>In 2016, the FCA reviewed IGCs and found that they were “generally effective” in influencing and advancing cost reductions for members. The review also found that the Independent Project Board’s work in auditing high legacy charges and implementing IGCs had been successful. As a result, a substantial majority of consumers received improved outcomes regarding costs and charges, with 1m consumers receiving reduced costs and charges.</p><p>The FCA has announced that it will undertake a further review of IGCs in 2019/20.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130880/answer",,,,,"262256 ; 262257","2019-06-13T13:34:39.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130880/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130880/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-06-10","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that (a) investment choices available to workplace pension customers are regularly reviewed by Independent Governance Committees and (b) those investment choices are aligned with the interests of customers.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","262255"
